(159, 1, '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '<p>Sorbact Gel dressings are used to prevent or eliminate infection in dry to low-exudating wounds, burns or fungal infections without the use of silver. Sorbact selectively binds and inactivates pathogenic microorganisms through a natural binding process. Sorbact technology builds on the physical forces that make two hydrophobic (water-repellent) particles bind together when in direct contact utilizing the binding force of surrounding water molecules. The green surface of Sorbact has a unique property that binds and inactivates pathogenic microorganisms. Microorganisms bind to Sorbact within 15-30 seconds of application and become inactivated creating a microbiological balance that is favorable for the wound healing process. Binding and inactivation continues until Sorbact is removed and replaced.</p>', 'Sorbact Gel', '<p>Sorbact Gel dressings are used to prevent or eliminate infection in dry to low-exudating wounds, burns and fungal infections without the use of silver. Sorbact selectively binds and inactivates pathogenic microorganisms through a natural binding process.</p>', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sorbact-gel', '', '', '2014-12-30 06:29:23', '2014-12-30 06:29:23', '', 0, 'http://admedonlinenew.dev:8888/?product=sorbact-gel', 0, 'product', '', 0),
