(163, 1, '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '<p>Hydrogel sheet designed for the breast provides scar reduction and improved healing after breast reconstruction or augmentation surgeries. Provides cooling relief after radiation or aesthetic treatments on face and neck.</p> <p>Spand-Gel primary wound hydrogel dressingd provide a moist and cool wound-healing environment to promote granulation tissue formation and relieve pain, burning, itching and soreness. Provides a barrier from exogenous bacteria and fluids and does not adhere to tissue.Â Â Spand-Gel absorbs wound exudates up to 3 times its weight.</p> <p>Spand-Gel comes in <span style="text-decoration: underline;">specialized shapes and sizes</span> to fit any area. This cool hydrogel sheet may be used in conjunction with MediSoothe Lotion. Best when cooled in the refrigerator for 30 minutes before using to provide soothing and cooling relief and a more comfortable recovery. This product may be rinsed off and placed in a zip-locked bag and refrigerated for later use.</p> <p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">www.meditechintl.com</span></p> <p>Secondary dressing required to hold in place. (see Spandage tapeless retention)</p>', 'Spand-Gel', '<p>Spand-Gel hydrogel dressings are shaped for the face, breast, neck and more. Provide a moist, cool wound-healing environment to promote granulation tissue formation, burn relief after radiation or aesthetic treatments and reduced scarring.</p>', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spand-gel', '', '', '2014-12-30 06:29:22', '2014-12-30 06:29:22', '', 0, 'http://admedonlinenew.dev:8888/?product=spand-gel', 0, 'product', '', 0),
