(171, 1, '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '2013-04-10 17:42:24', '<p>Normlgel is 0.9% Sodium Chloride (NaCl) solution in gel form. It donates moisture to the wound, maintains an optimal moist environment for wound healing and supports autolytic debridment. Normlgel may be used in granulating and open wounds such as pressure ulcers, venous ulcers, arterial leg ulcers, diabetic ulcers, superficial burns (1st and 2nd degree), and open surgical wounds. Normlgel may also be used on wounds covered with dry fibrin.</p> <p><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5em;">Secondary dressing required to hold in place.</span></p>', 'Normlgel', '<p>Donates moisture to the wound site for optimal wound healing.Â </p>', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'normlgel', '', '', '2014-12-30 06:29:22', '2014-12-30 06:29:22', '', 0, 'http://admedonlinenew.dev:8888/?product=normlgel', 0, 'product', '', 0),
